{
  "stem": "25651.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then another Goy would have to come and pump the organ because, you know, electrically driven organs, in those days, were still-- perhaps they were still-- already in existence, but it was-- this was-- this was one of the old, conventional organs where you had to sit on a stool, and you had to pump with your feet.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, all the kids wanted to pump the organ, and to my mother, this was [YIDDISH] Shabbat, you know?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the organ was on the balcony where the women sat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she would chase us away from pumping the organ.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you could then hear that the organ gave up, [LAUGHS] so some other kid had to step in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she got annoyed again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She wanted the organ done away with, and this was a conversation on the way home every Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And father always said, look, I'm not that important in this community.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if I tell them not to play the organ, and to do away with the organ altogether from the synagogue, they will call me a [INAUDIBLE], you know, because this is reform and we play the organ with the services.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Just as a sideline, in 1992, when we had the-- we had a-- a get together of Jews from [INAUDIBLE], which my brother, [?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Shragga, ?] organized in 1992.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Unfortunately, he couldn't make it at the time because he had a heart bypass operation and the wound on his leg didn't heal.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So just when the commemoration days were taking place, he couldn't come and I had to deputize for him to-- to sort of give the speeches and-- and talk.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when we got into the synagogue, the synagogue is now used as the town archive and the chief archivist is a Dr.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
